# Proxmox Lab — Claude Code Skills

Custom skills for managing the Proxmox Private Cloud Lab infrastructure.

## Skills

| Skill | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `proxmox-iac` | Generate Terraform + Ansible code for this environment |
| `node-role-builder` | Scaffold Ansible roles (raw module, Alpine constraints) |
| `proxmox-debug` | Diagnose and fix Terraform, Ansible, SSH, and Proxmox errors |
| `scale-policy-editor` | Manage scaling config and scale.sh wrapper script |

## Installation

Copy `.skill` files to your Claude Code skills directory, or extract the
skill folders into `.claude/skills/`.

## Environment Summary

- Proxmox VE 9.x running in VirtualBox on a single laptop
- Alpine Linux 3.19 VMs — no Python, no internet
- Only ONE VM runs at a time (7.7 GB RAM constraint)
- Terraform: `bpg/proxmox` provider (not telmate)
- Ansible: `raw` module only (no standard modules)
